children.subject: I'd do 170 -> 61c -> 186 in terms of maximizing your chance of getting in. However, as always adjustment period is never a guarantee, and these are all classes I think that generally fill up, so be prepared to pursue a backup.

history.content: 170 always takes everyone in the fall, this semester though i had trouble getting into 61c and 186 and know people who couldnt get into either, 186 even had a completely full wl this semester. I would for 61+186+ugba phase 1 and 170 phase 2.

I'm interested in taking 186, 61c, 170 in the fall along with a couple of UGBA classes that I have to waitlist in phase 1 to get in. So I'll have a spot for one of the 3 cs classes in phase 1, one in phase 2 and one in adjustment. Fortunately, I have EECS major reserved seats and priority enrollment on the first day of all enrollment periods. How should I spread these three classes over the three periods to max my chances of getting in?
